title: 15 Min High Intensity Elliptical Cardio Climber HIIT
description:
Who’s ready to sweat? If you have a cardio climber at home, join Sunny Trainer Sydney for 15 minutes of calorie-burning, heart-pumping intervals! Feel the burn in your glutes, hamstrings, calves, and quads as you push the pace, and challenge yourself through high levels of resistance. 

15 Min High Intensity Elliptical Cardio Climber HIIT
Workout Length: 15 Minutes
Workout Level: Intermediate
Sunny Trainer: Sydney Eaton 

WORKOUT DETAILS

💨 3:30 | Rest - 1 minute

END WORKOUT

comments: I'm using an Elliptical Cross Trainer! This hit me real good. I did it with Level 10 Resistance level, Really tried so hard. Completed it! My Thighs were burning so badly. After done the cooldown was so refreshing and cooling honestly, It felt i could go on forever... Thanks for the great workout! Will be doing this everyday!

Hi, Sydney. I a 65 year old male recovering from a fall that fractured my back, right heel, dislocated ankle and severely bruised left foot.

I workout "with you" 5 days a week every morning for the past 4 months on my elliptical.

I go through 3 sets starting with resistance of 8( my elliptical go from 1-24) and by 3rd set, I'm at maximum 24 resistance and end my daily workout.

Some days I feel like going another few rounds but, it makes no sense to me😅

Thanks for motivating me towards my recovery physically.

It sucks as is getting old, worse when injured and with limited mobility...really make me feel like an "old man"😂

Are you making any more new videos?🤔
Just received mine in the mail yesterday! Can't wait to get started💪💪💪
It's great work out and very fire 🔥
